bilingual.source: You use an axe to cut wood.
But now her name is Linda Wood.
bilingual.target: 但现在她的名字是琳达·伍德。

bilingual.source: My full name is Alan Luke Wood.
bilingual.target: 我的全名是艾伦·卢克·伍德。

bilingual.source: It's made of used wood and glass.
bilingual.target: 它是用旧木头和玻璃做的。

bilingual.source: You use an axe to cut wood or trees.
His full name is George Charles Wood.
bilingual.target: 他的全名是乔治·查尔斯·伍德。

bilingual.source: People call my father George Charles Wood, Junior.
bilingual.target: 人们称我父亲为乔治·查尔斯·伍德二世。

list.abstract: wood是一个英语单词，可以用作名词、动词和形容词，可以翻译为木材、树林等

yingyinNormal.en: Well done, Harry. Wood's just told us.
yingyinNormal.zh: 嘿，干得棒极了，哈利，伍德跟我们说了。

yingyinNormal.en: Get the wood. I can't cook shit without a fire.
yingyinNormal.zh: 捡柴火去，我没火也做不了饭啊。

yingyinNormal.en: Potter, this is Oliver Wood. Wood, I have found you a Seeker.
yingyinNormal.zh: 波特，这是奥利佛伍德，伍德，我给你找了一个找球手。

yingyinNormal.en: That's right. Red wood. With a space in the middle. Wood that is red.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是啊，红色的木头，简称就是，红木。

yingyinNormal.en: Is it behind that rotten pile of wood? I think that rotten pile of wood is the cafe.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是不是在那堆枯木后面？我觉得那堆枯木就是小餐厅。

yingyinNormal.en: And wood! You must remember to put wood blocks between the wire and the building's struts.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还有木头！千万记住在钢索和大楼支柱间放木块。

yingyinNormal.en: That way, when the building breathe, the wood will break but the wire won't explode and tear you in half. Okay. Wood.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如此一来，大楼摇晃时木头会破，但钢索不会断裂，把你切成两半。好，木头。

yingyinNormal.en: Place wood blocks between the cable and mast. Okay. The wood blocks act as buffer, so when masts flex, the wire won't snap.
yingyinNormal.zh: 把木块放在钢索和柱子中间。好。有木块当成缓冲柱子弯曲时，钢索才不会断裂。

yingyinNormal.en: We are near the nesting ground of the Amazon wood quail.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们已经接近亚马逊林鹑的栖息地。

yingyinNormal.en: Like wood for a fire. Green magic takes life to open the gate.
yingyinNormal.zh: 像木材用来生火一样，绿色魔法需要生命才能开门。

yingyinNormal.en: Now, see, I pitched them tents. I ain't chopping any more wood.
yingyinNormal.zh: 听着，帐篷都是我搭建起来的，我才不劈木头呢。

yingyinNormal.en: I suppose that field below Peckham wood could be made into a pitch.
yingyinNormal.zh: 佩卡姆林下面那块地也可以改造成球场吧。

yingyinNormal.en: You are Omaticaya now. You may make your bow from the wood of Hometree.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你现在是奥玛蒂卡亚族人了，你能用家园树的木头制作自己的弓。

yingyinNormal.en: It's called "Marble with Wood," and let's just say it's made entirely of marble.
yingyinNormal.zh: 雕塑名叫《大理石和"硬木"》，这么说吧，雕塑完全是大理石做的。

yingyinNormal.en: It's $12.50. Okay, so, do you make the pizzas in one of those wood-burning ovens?
yingyinNormal.zh: 12.5美元。好，你们做披萨是用烧木头的炉子吗？

yingyinNormal.en: But I can! You are just having to take away the piece of wood. Then I will have to…
yingyinNormal.zh: 这可不行！你得把木棍拿走不可。不然我就要……

yingyinNormal.en: They've all accepted except for Barnes at Wheelers Wood. He's sworn to his sister's wedding.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们都接受了邀请，除了惠勒伍德的巴恩斯，他得去参加妹妹的婚礼。

yingyinNormal.en: If you also have malaria and a deep distrust of Native Americans, we're really cooking with a wood stove.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果你还得了疟疾与十分不信任美洲原住民，我们就真是有地道的拓荒者风了。

yingyinNormal.en: Yes, Joey has a very careful screening process. Apparently, not everyone is qualified to own wood and nails.
yingyinNormal.zh: 乔伊有一套严格的筛选过程，并非每个人都适合拥有木制品。

yingyinNormal.en: Uniform's forgotten. You have no voice? You were enlist? I was sir, Belleau Wood. Twice decorated. I see it, sir.
yingyinNormal.zh: 仅剩制服，无权发声？你参战了？是的，长官。在贝洛伍德。两次授勋，我看到的，先生。

word_usage.usage: 说 "树林" 用 wood 或 woods 都可以。

examination_example.sentence: We need the forest's resources for <highlight>wood</highlight> and paper.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们需要森林中的木材和纸张资源。

examination_example.sentence: All of the pieces were made from used metal, <highlight>wood</highlight>, cloth, and plastic.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 所有的作品都是用用过的金属、木头、布和塑料制成的。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Wood</highlight>’s experience in China shared in his diaries.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 伍德在他的日记中分享了他在中国的经历。

examination_example.sentence: People paid enough attention to <highlight>Wood</highlight>’s news report.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人们对伍德的新闻报道给予了足够的关注。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Wood</highlight>’s diaries soon attracted the world’s attention.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 伍德的日记很快就引起了全世界的关注。

examination_example.sentence: I saw a path leading into some <highlight>woods</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我看到一条通往树林的小路。

examination_example.sentence: There was no sunlight in the farmer’s <highlight>wood</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 农夫的树林里没有阳光。

examination_example.sentence: Finally he planted the tree in his <highlight>woods</highlight> (树林) where no one could see it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 最后，他把这棵树种在没人能看到的树林里。
